cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image segmentation using a deep learning architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of autoencoders, which are commonly used in unsupervised learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of normalized cut, which is a graph-based segmentation technique, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses postprocessing involving conditional random field smoothing and hierarchical segmentation, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia analysis, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
